      <biogHist id="md5-493566d35afdb6ec65793dc9999f2dd6">
        <p>Psychologist, Administrator, 1912-  .  Douglas E. Smith began lecturing in psychology at the University in 1937.  He left (1941- 1946) to serve in the Canadian Army as personnel officer. Appointed full professor in 1949, he chaired the Department of Philosophy and Psychology between 1952 and 1958. Dr. Smith served as Dean of Arts from 1959 to 1972, retiring as Professor Emeritus in 1975.</p>
      </biogHist>
